               <p>JOHN SMITH. I live in the Commercial-road, and am a <rs id="t18320906-421-viclabel2371" type="occupation">captain of a vessel</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-421-victim3408 t18320906-421-viclabel2371"></join>. On the 8th of August, at half-past ten o'clock in the evening; I was walking in <placeName id="t18320906-421-crimeloc2372">Grenada-terrace, Commercial-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-421-crimeloc2372" type="placeName" value="Grenada-terrace, Commercial-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-421-crimeloc2372" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-421-off2369 t18320906-421-crimeloc2372"></join> - I felt a tug at my pocket, I turned and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand; I said, "You scoundrel what are you about?" he immediately ran away - a young gentleman took him; I went up and found him in possession of the officer: I took up my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-421-person3409">
                  THOMAS 
                  SMITHERS
               <interp inst="t18320906-421-person3409" type="surname" value="SMITHERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-421-person3409" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-421-person3409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable K 101). I was on duty, and saw the prisoner running - I took him; this handkerchief was picked up.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I turn the corner with it? A. I did not see you drop it; I saw you run and turn one corner: they were pursuing you - I did not lose sight of you.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
